Diagnosis. Opercular verticil consists of 5–6 triangular spines curved inward, with a small external knob. Dorsal verticil spine larger than others, with elongated sharp tip, curved inward. Funnel radii with 18–25 chitinized pointed tips, base of funnel half chitinized (
Fig. 11
). Tube often (but not always) bluish, dark brown or black inside.
